Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.10,0:00:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerful, pounding heart. Cheerful, pounding heart. \NCheerful, pounding heart. Cheerful, pounding heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerful, pounding heart. \NCheerful, pounding heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.95,0:00:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerful!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.12,0:00:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pounding!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.66,0:00:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.94,0:02:11.44,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know there was a place \Nlike this in Shinjuku...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:15.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,If a Machine Goodfellow activated in \Nthe middle of a big city like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.51,0:02:17.10,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,it'd be really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:22.96,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,The Machine Goodfellows are \Nmind-machine interfaces specifically tuned
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.96,0:02:26.32,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,to each designer child, to let \Nthem use mobile weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:31.42,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Designer children can use these personalized \Nmachines to control all the latest weaponry
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.42,0:02:33.96,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,as if it were an extension of their own bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.33,0:02:37.80,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,But there's something even more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.39,0:02:43.13,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Akari Yomatsuri acquired the \Nmain manual of this device,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.13,0:02:45.31,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,the Machine Goodfellow's hidden main system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:50.51,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,According to the manual,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:55.40,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,by loading a capsule filled with \NOrgone energy into the head,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.40,0:02:58.62,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,the consciousness of the designer child inside
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.62,0:03:01.41,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,can be transferred to a Kiltgang.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.36,0:03:06.95,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Orgone energy is what the \NKiltgang needs to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:09.32,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,Orgone energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.32,0:03:12.25,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,The energy released from the \NLivlaster is one type of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.83,0:03:16.32,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,The reason they tried to force \NHana to manifest the Livlaster
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.32,0:03:19.06,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,was to use its energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.06,0:03:20.76,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,We also learned
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.32,0:03:27.10,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,that once the Orgone energy capsule has \Nbeen loaded into a Machine Goodfellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.68,0:03:30.85,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,the energy transfer to the Kiltgang takes \Nthree minutes and fifty-nine seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:32.21,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:37.32,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,If you can blow its head off within those \Nthree minutes and fifty-nine seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:40.44,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,the Kiltgang won't be able to activate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.80,0:03:42.78,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,Three minutes and fifty-nine seconds...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:45.57,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,So the head is the weak point...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.88,0:03:49.54,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really impressed you learned \Nall this, Science Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:51.09,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.09,0:03:56.87,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I'm surprised Akari Yomatsuri was \Nable to infiltrate the enemy's systems
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.87,0:04:00.21,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,during the last battle and retrieve all this data.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.64,0:04:05.53,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a gentleman, \Nto say "retrieve" instead of "steal."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.02,0:04:08.07,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,So she's their weak point?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.76,0:04:13.14,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She's the pest who hacked the Machine Goodfellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:16.36,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't look like a fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.36,0:04:17.89,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Then she's our target.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.14,0:04:22.44,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She still looks like a little kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:26.78,Title,M,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(653,1)}Magical Girl Akari-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:45.84,SignA,,0000,0000,0000,,Ai's New Single \NIce Cream Love
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:55.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's even bigger than it looked online!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.79,0:05:04.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So good...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.09,0:05:07.38,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It really is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.38,0:05:10.41,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like we're always eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:12.20,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz, you have some, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:16.46,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, another Machine Goodfellow \Nwill activate nearby, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:17.87,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.87,0:05:22.51,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But Pitz says he doesn't know any more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.51,0:05:24.67,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That much alone is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.17,0:05:30.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If one does activate, we can \Nuse the MM bus to locate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.61,0:05:35.56,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Defeating it in three minutes and fifty-nine \Nseconds will be the main problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:37.48,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.47,0:05:40.53,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There are two kinds of close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:44.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A close win and a close loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.66,0:05:50.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just leave it to the magical girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:06:00.69,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Locating their Machine Goodfellow \Nahead of time would be best...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.68,0:06:05.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, there are a lot of \Npeople here, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:07.11,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:11.35,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A fight in the middle of a city \Nlike this would be bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:14.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt the enemy wants to \Nattract attention, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.98,0:06:17.52,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Finding them might be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:21.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:24.39,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.39,0:06:26.14,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A magic item...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.88,0:06:28.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to buy a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.13,0:06:31.49,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I broke mine during the last mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.86,0:06:33.95,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.95,0:06:35.55,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.55,0:06:37.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I know Shinjuku like the back of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:41.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And finding the Machine Goodfellow \Nis more important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:43.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:45.40,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.40,0:06:47.71,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can protect myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.71,0:06:52.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll be going AWOL to enjoy myself for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:54.92,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You take care of the rest, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.94,0:07:00.56,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, do you have to keep calling me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.71,0:07:05.91,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one not contributing to the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.53,0:07:12.49,SignB,,0000,0000,0000,,Nippon Seinenkan Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:15.45,SignC,,0000,0000,0000,,Ai Summer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.93,0:07:15.45,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to sing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.04,0:07:19.20,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid to sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:20.84,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:28.55,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,That refers to your stance regarding \Nyour long-term career as an idol,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:31.43,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,not strictly to tonight's concert, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.12,0:07:36.26,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Ai...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:37.33,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.33,0:07:38.38,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Pounding!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.38,0:07:40.60,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.60,0:07:43.77,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that your catchphrase?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:47.63,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone loses confidence in \Nthemselves once in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:49.61,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,I've never had any self-confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:52.03,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:54.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We've both worked so hard to reach this point!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:07:59.20,SignD,,0000,0000,0000,,A Popular Idol's {\c&HFFFFFF&}Lonely Past
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:01.79,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You saw that magazine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.61,0:08:06.75,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Ignore what the magazines say!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:09.88,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Her cheerfulness is fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.75,0:08:09.88,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You grew up in an orphanage, \Nand never went to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.26,0:08:12.02,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.02,0:08:15.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Idols are supposed to be special...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:18.49,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, having something that makes \Nyou different is a great weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.30,0:08:20.88,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:25.61,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,What if everyone hates me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.05,0:08:29.57,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Would I be all alone again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.00,0:08:36.58,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If they really didn't like you, no one \Nwould come to your concerts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.58,0:08:39.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight's another full house, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.23,0:08:44.46,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'm just not cut out to be an idol...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:46.76,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.76,0:08:50.36,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,New girls enter the industry all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.50,0:08:54.68,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, are you interested in being an idol?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:57.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a scout for a talent agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.06,0:09:02.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're interested in me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:03.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You have a good eye...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.26,0:09:06.60,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.37,0:09:08.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The dealer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:39.97,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.51,0:09:50.48,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, are you okay, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.48,0:09:51.38,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.38,0:09:53.94,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,You must really love her, man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:56.54,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your magic item.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:02.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we've used every trick \Nin the book to come this far,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.47,0:10:05.04,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,but it all depends on how her next CD sells...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.98,0:10:07.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She's lost confidence in herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.87,0:10:10.75,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be tough to keep going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.43,0:10:14.58,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I think she has talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.00,0:10:17.93,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Ai-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.48,0:10:27.31,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Your manager was telling her boss that \Nthey're nearly through with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.16,0:10:29.94,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with the theater staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.41,0:10:33.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look like I'm with the theater staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.72,0:10:35.75,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.75,0:10:38.90,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,If you come in without permission, \Nsecurity will get mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:40.84,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you could say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.96,0:10:45.37,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a scout.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:16.09,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Malkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:19.82,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,How does it feel to be awake, Aiatar?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.00,0:11:26.38,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take away your cheer like a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:37.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.10,0:11:40.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I can't reach Akari...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.07,0:11:41.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.99,0:11:44.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was going to buy a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:48.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And you let her go off on her own, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.47,0:11:50.97,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're calling me that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:53.40,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do you normally turn off your \Nphone when you're shopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.75,0:11:56.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I bet she's off playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.87,0:12:14.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, script kiddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:18.09,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, she's a magical girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.03,0:12:21.30,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A magical girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.62,0:12:26.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she calls herself, \Nso that's what she must be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.51,0:12:28.57,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:30.43,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A magical girl, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.50,0:12:40.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Akari hasn't returned yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.64,0:12:44.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The time Hana predicted is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.03,0:12:47.66,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Without Akari, the operation will be less effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.21,0:12:50.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where's she gone off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.42,0:12:52.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,She needs to realize her position.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.35,0:12:54.18,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akari isn't like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:12:59.80,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,When there's a job for her, \Nshe always does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:03.26,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.74,0:13:06.31,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be standing by in the Ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.66,0:13:12.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You're right... I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.74,0:13:16.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Has something happened to Akari?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.34,0:13:23.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I really hate all those Globe Impacters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.02,0:13:26.95,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, magical girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.26,0:13:33.42,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you use your magic power \Nto put them all out of commission?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.21,0:13:39.58,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We know you have the skills to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.85,0:13:49.97,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Do it now, magical girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:53.93,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.25,0:14:04.53,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,A concert with no audience, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:10.32,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of sad, but I guess it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.04,0:14:16.52,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Abreaction!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.48,0:14:29.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,MM bus signal detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:31.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.70,0:14:38.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjuku Development Zone 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.67,0:14:40.60,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Begin the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.97,0:14:42.56,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You can't make it that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:45.82,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And that's probably an artillery type.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.82,0:14:48.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If it sees you, it'll shoot you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.71,0:14:50.97,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lot better than fighting \Nin the middle of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:52.66,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Just do it, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.77,0:14:54.87,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:56.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:14:57.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.52,0:14:59.16,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Initiating launch sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.91,0:15:40.33,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.95,0:15:41.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:44.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine Ordinary, launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:52.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't going to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.23,0:15:54.97,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.48,0:15:56.86,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The captain will make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.68,0:16:00.43,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Livlaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.50,0:16:26.00,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,You're a wimp.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.53,0:16:32.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.37,0:16:36.03,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,No more bets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.30,0:16:39.39,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,He's hiding behind the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.85,0:16:43.06,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, if time runs out, we win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.06,0:16:46.27,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Cheerful artillery... Totally invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.27,0:16:48.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't coming to finish him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.31,0:16:50.15,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They realize it just needs to become a Kiltgang?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:54.80,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Will we have to submit a request \Nfor the low-orbit Impacters?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.16,0:16:57.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.28,0:17:00.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The low-orbit Impacters are being hacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:03.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sixty percent are off-line!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.90,0:17:05.25,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.60,0:17:06.73,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.73,0:17:09.54,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Now Globe's Impacters can't activate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.99,0:17:14.38,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if she can \Nbecome a Kiltgang, we win.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:19.55,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We're running out of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.45,0:17:22.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hiding is pointless...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.27,0:17:23.14,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.14,0:17:25.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you go out there, they'll shoot you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.37,0:17:31.40,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's close, I have to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.64,0:17:33.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,There are only two types of close.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:34.86,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, don't you, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:37.03,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:50.67,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.63,0:17:54.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He's out of weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.26,0:17:57.72,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,The end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.72,0:17:59.40,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I still have one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.85,0:18:05.31,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that it's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.18,0:18:09.90,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Time's up, Neoteny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:12.84,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Pierce through it, Livlaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.32,0:18:20.12,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:45.71,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That was close, in a lot of ways...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.98,0:18:52.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What about Akari?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.84,0:18:59.99,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,He got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:04.15,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Whining. Whimpering. Miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.10,0:19:07.08,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I can still make it to the concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.22,0:19:11.43,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,I love my fans so much, I want to eat them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.07,0:19:13.85,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll sing for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.69,0:19:21.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hi! This is your lovey-dovey bunny!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.49,0:19:22.21,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.24,0:19:24.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.19,0:19:26.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yup...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.49,0:19:28.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I see, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.58,0:19:35.60,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Aiatar screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.60,0:19:36.44,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.06,0:19:45.62,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,To get even, maybe we'll have her make \Nall the Globe bases self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.47,0:19:49.33,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, can't you, magical girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.28,0:19:56.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, over ninety percent of the \Nlow-orbit Impacters are off-line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.45,0:19:58.60,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Does Akari have something to do with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.37,0:20:03.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good chance the enemy is using
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.80,0:20:06.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,her skills and knowledge of Globe's secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.86,0:20:11.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Another group is trying to trace her \Nlocation via the route of the breach,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:15.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,but she's bounced off a lot of servers, \Nso they can't trace her...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:18.11,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.84,0:20:22.20,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have let her go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.61,0:20:32.85,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Is it done?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.14,0:20:35.32,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.32,0:20:37.84,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Have you done what I ordered you to?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.76,0:20:42.05,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If I could have avoided it, I'd have \Npreferred not to use this magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:47.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I can only use it once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.75,0:20:51.72,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A second time, and they'll be watching \Nfor it, so it won't work...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.72,0:20:53.39,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:57.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,All the nuclear weapons aboard \Nthe low-orbit Impacters,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.11,0:21:02.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,as well as every Russian, Chinese, and American \Nnuclear missile, will all launch at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.99,0:21:06.62,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't release me in ten minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.62,0:21:08.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,the whole Earth will become a wasteland.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.06,0:21:11.61,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.61,0:21:14.21,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, humanity will be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.60,0:21:16.88,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei's a good, honest kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.88,0:21:22.25,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And he told me that the Planetary Gears
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.25,0:21:26.34,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,came to the Solar System and \Nwaited for humanity to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.18,0:21:30.52,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And that you couldn't bear waiting anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:36.28,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If the missiles are launched, \Nhumanity will be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.28,0:21:38.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But all that means for them is death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.22,0:21:41.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.96,0:21:48.41,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,but how long will you have to wait before \Nanother sentient source of Orgone energy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.46,0:21:52.16,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,evolves in this Solar System?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:54.53,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A few hundred million years?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.53,0:21:56.85,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A few billion years?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.99,0:22:08.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Crap... She's serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:11.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She's really going to launch the nukes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.24,0:22:11.80,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.12,0:22:34.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'll tell you one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.44,0:22:43.00,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you aliens can beat a magical girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:19.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights rush to \Nrepair the damaged Earth Engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.11,0:24:23.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,but the Planetary Gears quickly activate \Na new Machine Goodfellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.79,0:24:25.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,In the midst of a fierce battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.27,0:24:28.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,the Earth Engine finally lets an enemy escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.19,0:24:29.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What will Teppei do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.86,0:24:33.28,Default,narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 10 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.28,0:24:35.62,Title2,narr,0000,0000,0000,,On the Windy Planet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.91,0:24:35.62,Default,narr,0000,0000,0000,,On the Windy Planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.96,0:24:38.28,Default,narr,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, scramble!
